==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pronghorn
<hw>Prong"horn`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An American antelope (<spn>Antilocapra Americana</spn>), native of
the plain near the Rocky Mountains. The upper parts are mostly yellowish
brown; the under parts, the sides of the head and throat, and the
buttocks, are white. The horny sheath of the horns is shed annually.
Called also <altname>cabr⟦eacute⟧e</altname>, <altname>cabut</altname>,
<altname>prongbuck</altname>, and <altname>pronghorned
antelope</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>pronk</ent>⟦br⟧
